tags.name: Adado Riverfront Park
tags.note: Brett Kaschinske, Parks Director for the City of Lansing, stated in an email, "All city owed land South of Oakland Ave on both sides of the River is considered [Adado] Riverfront Park and we consider this one park Burchard begins at Oakland Ave and
tags.note_2: is on both sides of the river. We consider this one park." I have interpreted this to mean city land bounded by Oakland to the North, Grand and Center to the West and East and Rotary park to the South is all Adado Riverfront Park. I have also
tags.note_3: interpreted it to mean that the river is not part of the park.
